Package gov.nasa.gsfc.nisgs.nsls

Class Summary
Log This class is used by a client of the logging system to log events.
Log.Parameters Parameters classes must be subclassed from this abstract class.
Log.Source Event source classes must be subclassed from this abstract class.
LogEvent  
LoggableThrowable This class exists to hold static methods for converting a random Throwable into a vanilla Throwable that can be safely serialized, sent to the NSLS logger, and (this is the important part) correctly deserialized.
LogPrinter This class connects to an SLS server and prints its log messages in a tab-delimited text format, optionally filtered by date/time and message type.
LogReader This class is used by a client of the logging system to read log events.
